{
  "video_id": "tc3If-zo_h4",
  "title": "Learn 10 Ways to Use the English Verb \"To be\" in the Imperative",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 740.0,
      "end_time": 2420.0,
      "text": "Hi Bob the Canadian here."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2420.0,
      "end_time": 6899.0,
      "text": "Sometimes in English you need to be able to tell someone what to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6899.0,
      "end_time": 12700.0,
      "text": "This verb form is called the imperative, and in this video we're going to look at 10 ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 12700.0,
      "end_time": 22920.0,
      "text": "to use the verb, \"to be\" in its imperative form."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22920.0,
      "end_time": 24570.0,
      "text": "1. Be careful!"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 24570.0,
      "end_time": 30460.0,
      "text": "You can say, \"Be careful!\" to someone if they are doing something dangerous."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30460.0,
      "end_time": 36290.0,
      "text": "Imagine you and a friend are mountain climbing, and as your friend climbs above you, you see"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36290.0,
      "end_time": 39589.0,
      "text": "that he is in a dangerous situation."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39590.0,
      "end_time": 42500.0,
      "text": "You could say, using the imperative:"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42500.0,
      "end_time": 43370.0,
      "text": "Be careful!"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43370.0,
      "end_time": 44960.0,
      "text": "Be careful up there Dave."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44960.0,
      "end_time": 46300.0,
      "text": "You might slip."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46300.0,
      "end_time": 47839.0,
      "text": "Be careful Dave."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47840.0,
      "end_time": 50400.0,
      "text": "It looks dangerous up there."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51220.0,
      "end_time": 53230.0,
      "text": "2. Be quiet."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53230.0,
      "end_time": 57230.0,
      "text": "Imagine you are driving in a van and you have a bunch of your children in the back if you"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 57230.0,
      "end_time": 60169.0,
      "text": "have children and they are being loud."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60170.0,
      "end_time": 66159.0,
      "text": "You could use the imperative phrase, \"Be quiet!\" to tell them that they are being too loud"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66159.0,
      "end_time": 69200.0,
      "text": "and you would like them to quiet down."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69200.0,
      "end_time": 70549.0,
      "text": "Be quiet kids!"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 70549.0,
      "end_time": 73909.0,
      "text": "I'm trying to concentrate on my driving."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73909.0,
      "end_time": 75540.0,
      "text": "Be quiet kids!"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75540.0,
      "end_time": 77859.0,
      "text": "It's too loud in here."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 79300.0,
      "end_time": 81150.0,
      "text": "3. Be prepared."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81150.0,
      "end_time": 86109.0,
      "text": "Let's imagine that a storm is approaching and you are listening to the news."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 86109.0,
      "end_time": 90530.0,
      "text": "On the news the news anchor may say: Be prepared!"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 90530.0,
      "end_time": 92119.0,
      "text": "A storm is coming."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 92119.0,
      "end_time": 93829.0,
      "text": "Be prepared people!"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 93829.0,
      "end_time": 96249.0,
      "text": "High winds are imminent."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96249.0,
      "end_time": 97280.0,
      "text": "Be prepared!"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 97280.0,
      "end_time": 99819.0,
      "text": "A storm will arrive soon."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 99819.0,
      "end_time": 104929.0,
      "text": "And this is the imperative form of \"to be\" with the word prepared."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 104929.0,
      "end_time": 110490.0,
      "text": "Letting you know that you should make sure you have food, candles, and other things you"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110490.0,
      "end_time": 113759.0,
      "text": "may need in the event of a disaster."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113760.0,
      "end_time": 115760.0,
      "text": "Be prepared!"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 115920.0,
      "end_time": 118800.0,
      "text": "4. Be happy!"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 118900.0,
      "end_time": 121490.0,
      "text": "You might know the song, \"Don't worry."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 121490.0,
      "end_time": 122490.0,
      "text": "Be happy!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 122490.0,
      "end_time": 125909.0,
      "text": "And this song actually uses two sentences in the imperative."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125909.0,
      "end_time": 129250.0,
      "text": "The first is the negative form, \"Don't worry.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129250.0,
      "end_time": 133270.0,
      "text": "and the second is the affirmative form, \"Be happy!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 133270.0,
      "end_time": 139610.0,
      "text": "And basically it is telling you that you should set aside your worries in life, don't think"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139610.0,
      "end_time": 143620.0,
      "text": "about your problems, and just try to be happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143620.0,
      "end_time": 144620.0,
      "text": "Don't worry."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 144620.0,
      "end_time": 145790.0,
      "text": "Be happy!"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 147130.0,
      "end_time": 148400.0,
      "text": "5. Don't be late."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148400.0,
      "end_time": 153700.0,
      "text": "So I've switched over to using the negative form of the imperative."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153700.0,
      "end_time": 157720.0,
      "text": "In the affirmative form we say things like, \"Be happy!\"."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 157720.0,
      "end_time": 162270.0,
      "text": "In the negative form we say things with, \"Don't\" in front."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162270.0,
      "end_time": 165430.0,
      "text": "So we would say things like, \"Don't be late.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 165430.0,
      "end_time": 172260.0,
      "text": "So imagine you are a teacher and you and your students are going to go on a trip."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 172260.0,
      "end_time": 173940.0,
      "text": "You would say to your students:"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173940.0,
      "end_time": 175840.0,
      "text": "Don't be late tomorrow morning."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 175840.0,
      "end_time": 178260.0,
      "text": "We are leaving at 7am."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 178260.0,
      "end_time": 182109.0,
      "text": "Don't be late because the bus will not wait for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 182110.0,
      "end_time": 183640.0,
      "text": "Don't be late."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 185600.0,
      "end_time": 187900.0,
      "text": "6. Don't be mean."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 187900.0,
      "end_time": 193970.0,
      "text": "You might be talking with a brother or sister and maybe it's turning into an argument and"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 193970.0,
      "end_time": 199730.0,
      "text": "one of you is starting to get angry and saying words that they should not say."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 199730.0,
      "end_time": 200980.0,
      "text": "You could say:"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 200980.0,
      "end_time": 202260.0,
      "text": "Don't be mean."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 202260.0,
      "end_time": 205310.0,
      "text": "Don't be mean to me when you talk."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 205310.0,
      "end_time": 210500.0,
      "text": "And this is again the negative form of the imperative and you're indicating to the person"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 210500.0,
      "end_time": 213790.0,
      "text": "that you would prefer that they are kind to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 213790.0,
      "end_time": 215230.0,
      "text": "Don't be mean."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 215230.0,
      "end_time": 217310.0,
      "text": "Let's keep this argument civil."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 217310.0,
      "end_time": 218750.0,
      "text": "Don't be mean."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 220900.0,
      "end_time": 221350.0,
      "text": "7. Don't be afraid."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 221350.0,
      "end_time": 224530.0,
      "text": "Imagine you're walking with a small child and it's nighttime."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 224530.0,
      "end_time": 226840.0,
      "text": "And it's kind of dark outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 226840.0,
      "end_time": 228710.0,
      "text": "You would say to the child:"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 228710.0,
      "end_time": 229780.0,
      "text": "Don't be afraid."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 229780.0,
      "end_time": 231980.0,
      "text": "I am here with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 231980.0,
      "end_time": 232980.0,
      "text": "Don't be afraid."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 232980.0,
      "end_time": 235119.0,
      "text": "I will hold your hand."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 235120.0,
      "end_time": 241950.0,
      "text": "And in this way you use the imperative to indicate to the child how they should be feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 241950.0,
      "end_time": 247100.0,
      "text": "It won't necessarily stop them from being afraid, but it might assure them that you"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 247100.0,
      "end_time": 249700.0,
      "text": "are watching over them."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 249700.0,
      "end_time": 250600.0,
      "text": "Don't be afraid."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 251930.0,
      "end_time": 253790.0,
      "text": "8. Don't be difficult."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 253790.0,
      "end_time": 258918.0,
      "text": "Sometimes when having a small argument with a friend who you know really well, you might"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 258918.0,
      "end_time": 260430.0,
      "text": "say to them:"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 260430.0,
      "end_time": 261549.0,
      "text": "Don't be difficult."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261548.0,
      "end_time": 265830.0,
      "text": "If they are making the argument somewhat uncomfortable for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 265830.0,
      "end_time": 269378.0,
      "text": "You would need to know the person well to make this statement."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269379.0,
      "end_time": 275539.0,
      "text": "But let's say for instance a friend was bugging me, or making fun of me about something."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 275539.0,
      "end_time": 277498.0,
      "text": "I could say to them:"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277499.0,
      "end_time": 279790.0,
      "text": "Dave, don't be difficult."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 279790.0,
      "end_time": 283160.0,
      "text": "Let's try to resolve this nicely."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 284789.0,
      "end_time": 286860.0,
      "text": "9. Don't be an idiot."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 286860.0,
      "end_time": 293940.0,
      "text": "Please don't ever say this sentence to someone, but you should know what this sentence is."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 293940.0,
      "end_time": 299430.0,
      "text": "Sometimes when you are watching a TV show or a movie you will hear someone say something"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 299430.0,
      "end_time": 300430.0,
      "text": "like:"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 300430.0,
      "end_time": 301639.0,
      "text": "Don't be an idiot."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 301639.0,
      "end_time": 307360.0,
      "text": "And basically what this means is they think the person is acting in a way where they are"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 307360.0,
      "end_time": 310280.0,
      "text": "showing that they are not intelligent."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 310280.0,
      "end_time": 315989.0,
      "text": "And so they would say in derogatory way, it is a bit of an insult:"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 315990.0,
      "end_time": 317139.0,
      "text": "Don't be an idiot."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 317139.0,
      "end_time": 320690.0,
      "text": "Again, please don't use this sentence yourself."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 320690.0,
      "end_time": 322259.0,
      "text": "This is only so you will recognize it."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 322259.0,
      "end_time": 328250.0,
      "text": "But the phrase, \"Don't be an idiot.\" is something you will hear sometimes in English."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 329699.0,
      "end_time": 331789.0,
      "text": "10. Let's be kind to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 331789.0,
      "end_time": 337680.0,
      "text": "So this is the form of the imperative that includes the person who is speaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 337680.0,
      "end_time": 344650.0,
      "text": "When we use, \"Let's\" in front of an imperative sentence it means that I myself as the speaker"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 344650.0,
      "end_time": 346830.0,
      "text": "am included in the command."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 346830.0,
      "end_time": 348430.0,
      "text": "So if I say:"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 348430.0,
      "end_time": 350250.0,
      "text": "Let's be kind to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 350250.0,
      "end_time": 355469.0,
      "text": "It means that myself and the other people that I am talking to will all attempt to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 355469.0,
      "end_time": 358279.0,
      "text": "kind to each other in the conversation."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 358279.0,
      "end_time": 359509.0,
      "text": "Let's be kind to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 359509.0,
      "end_time": 363300.0,
      "text": "Those are actually good words for everyone around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 363300.0,
      "end_time": 367639.0,
      "text": "Well that's 10 ways to use the verb, \"to be\" in the imperative."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 367639.0,
      "end_time": 369289.0,
      "text": "Bob the Canadian here."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 369289.0,
      "end_time": 370979.0,
      "text": "Learn English with Bob the Canadian."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 370979.0,
      "end_time": 375349.0,
      "text": "Thank you once again for watching if you don't mind hitting the like button below, the thumb's"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 375349.0,
      "end_time": 380248.0,
      "text": "up button that would be awesome for me, and if you haven't yet subscribed to my channel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 380249.0,
      "end_time": 381249.0,
      "text": "please subscribe."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 381249.0,
      "end_time": 386590.0,
      "text": "I make video lesson once or twice per week just to help you learn English."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 386590.0,
      "end_time": 387590.0,
      "text": "Have a great day."
    }
  ]
}